<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Hestan service</p>
    <h2>Hestan Outdoor: 70+ Michelin Stars of commercial pedigree, applied to residential.</h2>

    <p>Hestan Outdoor is part of Hestan Commercial Corporation, the same American manufacturer powering kitchens that have collectively earned 70+ Michelin Stars. The Hestan Outdoor lineup applies that commercial-kitchen engineering pedigree to residential outdoor cooking. Made in the USA. 304 grade stainless steel construction. The signature Trellis Burner™, 321 stainless tubular design, 3rd-party tested for 500 hours of durability.</p>

    <p>Hestan grills start around $4,800 for the entry GABR30 and reach $11,300+ for the flagship GMBR42 with rotisserie. Pricing is competitive with Lynx Professional, Fire Magic Echelon, and Wolf Outdoor. What you get is different: 9 color options (no other premium grill brand offers this), DiamondCut lasered cooking grates, Stadium motion-activated under-hood lighting, Horizon spring-assist hood hinges that hold at any height, salamander-positioned multipurpose IR rotisserie burner with 50-lb capacity.</p>

    <p>We see Hestan grills in Beverly Hills, Newport Beach, Pacific Palisades, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and Bel Air outdoor kitchens. Often paired with Hestan indoor ranges (Hestan Indoor offers 30,000 BTU per burner, the most powerful single residential burner in the US market). Owners who buy Hestan typically buy the full Hestan kitchen experience: outdoor plus indoor plus sometimes Hestan Cookware.</p>

    <p>Our techs service all current Hestan Outdoor configurations: GABR (all Trellis), GMBR (Sear plus Trellis hybrid, the most popular), GSBR (all Sear). All three sizes (30, 36, 42 inch). All cart configurations: GCD30 double door, GCR42 drawer and door, CX2 deluxe with double side burner. Built-in and freestanding.</p>

    <p>BHGS #A49573. Same-day across LA, Orange County, Ventura. EPA 608 certified for any outdoor refrigeration on the same property. Trellis Burner™ replacement parts and Hot Surface Igniter (OEM 006096) carried on the van for most service calls.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP & WHAT FAILS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Lineup and architecture</p>
    <h2>Hestan series and what fails on each.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Hestan Outdoor splits across three burner configurations within each size class. The configuration determines flame flexibility versus searing power. We identify by serial number first, not just model badge.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">GABR (All Trellis Burners)</h3>
    <p>No infrared sear burner. Pure Trellis Burner™ cooking experience for owners who want maximum flame flexibility. Trellis burners run from low simmer to high heat. Sizes: GABR30, GABR36, GABR42. Available in natural gas (-NG) and liquid propane (-LP) variants.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">GMBR (Sear plus Trellis hybrid)</h3>
    <p>One Trellis burner is replaced with a ceramic infrared sear burner. The most popular Hestan configuration. Combines Trellis flexibility with high-temp searing capability. Sizes: GMBR30, GMBR36, GMBR42. The GMBR36 puts out 89,000 total BTU (2 Trellis at 25,000 each plus IR sear at 25,000 plus IR top at 14,000). GMBR42 reaches 100,000+ BTU with three Trellis plus IR sear plus IR top.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">GSBR (All Sear Burners)</h3>
    <p>All infrared ceramic sear burners. No Trellis burners. High-temp searing focus, less flame flexibility but more searing power across the full grill surface. Sizes: GSBR30, GSBR36, GSBR42.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">AGCK-SB Sear Burner Conversion Kit</h3>
    <p>If you have a GABR and later want sear capability, the AGCK-SB Sear Burner Conversion Kit allows authorized installation of a sear burner replacing one Trellis. Effectively converts a GABR to a GMBR configuration in the field. Faster and cheaper than buying a new grill. We do these installs.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Sizes and cart configurations</h3>
    <p><strong>30 inch</strong> built-in or freestanding, two main burners, entry size. <strong>36 inch</strong> built-in or freestanding, three main burners, the most popular size. <strong>42 inch</strong> built-in or freestanding, four main burners, flagship.</p>
    <p>Cart options for freestanding: <strong>GCD30</strong> (double door cart, 30 inch only), <strong>GCR42</strong> (drawer and door cart, 42 inch only), <strong>CX2</strong> designation (deluxe cart with double side burner, e.g. GMBR42CX2 and GSBR42CX2).</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Common failures</h3>
    <p>In rough order of frequency on Hestan service calls: hot surface igniter failure (OEM 006096, single zone won't light), Trellis Burner™ pinhole at 10 to 15 years coastal, Stadium under-hood LED light failure (motion-activated bars, sized 30/36/42 with different part numbers per width), Horizon spring-assist hood hinges losing pressure at 7 to 10 years, DiamondCut cooking grate replacement at 10 to 15 inland or 8 to 12 coastal, time delay relay (10A 8 second) at 8 to 10 years, ceramic IR sear burner replacement at 5 to 8 years on heavy-use GMBR/GSBR, salamander rotisserie chain drive wear at 10 to 15 years, multipurpose IR top burner replacement at 10 to 12 years, AGIJ30/36/42 insulated jacket replacement when the original cabinet jacket is damaged.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TYPICAL SCENARIOS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top Hestan repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on Hestan service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Hot surface igniter element replacement (OEM 006096).</strong> Universal across Trellis and Sear burners. 30-minute swap once the part is on hand. Same part for both burner types, which trips up shops that order separately.</li>
      <li><strong>Trellis Burner™ replacement.</strong> 321 stainless burner with pinhole. Per-zone replacement. Trellis burners are integral to grill performance and must be used together, you cannot run a partial Trellis configuration.</li>
      <li><strong>Stadium LED light bar replacement.</strong> Model-specific (different part for 30, 36, 42 inch widths). Coastal moisture failures most common at 5 to 8 years.</li>
      <li><strong>Horizon hood spring replacement.</strong> Gas spring loses pressure at 7 to 10 years. Replacement restores hood-at-any-height function.</li>
      <li><strong>Time delay relay replacement.</strong> 10A, 8-second relay in ignition system. Less common but happens at 8 to 10 years.</li>
      <li><strong>Ceramic IR sear burner replacement.</strong> High-cycle thermal stress causes failure at 5 to 8 years. GMBR or GSBR configuration only (GABR has no sear burner).</li>
      <li><strong>DiamondCut cooking grate replacement.</strong> Wear-driven replacement at 8 to 15 years. Lasered 5/16 inch stainless replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>AGCK-SB Sear Burner Conversion.</strong> Owners with GABR who want sear capability install the conversion kit. We do these. Converts a GABR to effectively a GMBR configuration without buying a new grill.</li>
      <li><strong>Salamander rotisserie service.</strong> Chain-drive motor service or replacement. Concealed location requires partial cabinet disassembly. Quieter than belt drive but chain wears at 10 to 15 years.</li>
      <li><strong>Insulated jacket installation or replacement.</strong> AGIJ30, AGIJ36, AGIJ42 for built-in installations in combustible enclosures. Required for safety and warranty compliance.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five Hestan jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills, Hestan GMBR42-NG built-in (2020 install)</h3>
        <p>Middle Trellis Burner™ not lighting. Tested OEM 006096 hot surface igniter on that zone: failed. Replaced igniter. Tested ignition cycle. Working. Total: $120 plus $185 part plus 30 minutes = $335. 5-year igniter life is typical for inland install.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Newport Beach, Hestan GMBR36-LP built-in (2018 install)</h3>
        <p>Multi-zone issues at 7 years coastal. Diagnosed: 2 of 3 hot surface igniters failed (coastal salt accelerates element life), Trellis Burner™ left zone had pinhole starting. Replaced 2 igniters (OEM 006096), replaced left Trellis burner. Total: $120 plus $720 parts plus 1.5 hours = $940. Owner happy with 7-year coastal service interval, comparable life to what his neighbor's Lynx needed at year 6.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Calabasas, Hestan GABR36-NG built-in with AGCK-SB conversion (2021 install)</h3>
        <p>Owner wanted sear capability added to all-Trellis GABR. Installed AGCK-SB Sear Burner Conversion Kit, replacing one Trellis with ceramic IR sear burner. 2.5 hours including testing. Total: $120 plus $480 conversion kit plus $290 labor = $890. Effectively converted GABR to GMBR configuration without buying a new grill ($4,800+ saved).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pacific Palisades, Hestan GMBR42 with rotisserie (2017 install)</h3>
        <p>Stadium under-hood lights stopped working. Diagnosed: LED light bar harness corroded at the connector (coastal moisture at 8 years). Replaced 42 inch LED light bar service assembly. Tested motion activation. Working. Total: $120 plus $340 part plus 45 minutes = $505.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hidden Hills, Hestan GMBR42-NG with GCR42 cart freestanding (2022 install)</h3>
        <p>Multipurpose IR top burner not igniting for rotisserie use. Diagnosed: salamander-position IR top burner had failed. Replaced IR rotisserie burner. Tested rotisserie cycle with broiling pan. Working. Total: $120 plus $590 part plus 1.5 hours = $810. 3-year-old grill, premature failure, processed warranty claim through Hestan customer care for parts cost reimbursement.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2>What we do for Hestan, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>All Hestan Outdoor configurations (GABR All Trellis, GMBR Sear plus Trellis, GSBR All Sear)</li>
      <li>All sizes (30, 36, 42 inch)</li>
      <li>All cart configurations (GCD30 double door, GCR42 drawer and door, CX2 deluxe with double side burner)</li>
      <li>Built-in and freestanding variants</li>
      <li>Both natural gas (-NG) and liquid propane (-LP) variants</li>
      <li>Trellis Burner™ replacement and service (321 stainless tubular)</li>
      <li>Ceramic IR sear burner service</li>
      <li>Multipurpose IR rotisserie burner (salamander-positioned, 50-lb capacity)</li>
      <li>AGCK-SB Sear Burner Conversion Kit installation (Trellis to Sear field conversion)</li>
      <li>Stadium motion-activated under-hood LED lighting service</li>
      <li>Horizon spring-assist hood hinge replacement</li>
      <li>DiamondCut cooking grate replacement</li>
      <li>Insulated jacket installation and replacement (AGIJ30, AGIJ36, AGIJ42)</li>
      <li>Hestan Cooktop and Indoor range cross-service when the same property has both</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new Hestan Outdoor grill installation (Hestan Commercial uses an authorized dealer network, typically estate-grade installs through Hestan's design ambassador program); custom Hestan modular cabinetry construction (installed by certified outdoor kitchen builders); Hestan Cookware repair (consumer product, not appliance); Hestan Vineyards anything (separate consumer wine business in Napa Valley).</p>

    <p>For warranty repairs on Hestan components, we document the failure on-site and process claims through Hestan customer care. Hestan also operates an Anaheim, CA outlet for discontinued and open-box items at up to 65 percent off. We can refer you there if you need a replacement component that's no longer manufactured.</p>
  </div>
</section>

